      en: "If you had been standing there in the stadium in Chonburi, Thailand, you could have felt it: the tension, the adrenaline and finally the eruption of joy when Isa Warps scored the equalizer. This was a moment forever etched in memory.\n\n## What are the SEA Games?\n\nThe SEA Games are the great sporting celebration of Southeast Asia. Athletes from dozens of countries come together and compete on one grand sporting stage. It's like the Olympic Games, but with that extra Southeast Asian fire. Every goal makes an entire nation cheer.\n\nFor women's football, this means stadium after stadium full of energy, color and supporters singing and jumping for their teams. And among all those teams stood Indonesia, with Isa Warps, ready to shine.\n\n## Isa Warps at the SEA Games 2025\n\nThey didn't start as favorites, but what this team showed was courage. Against Singapore, Indonesia was initially under pressure, and that tension was palpable. And then, in the 31st minute, Isa Warps struck: 1-1. The entire team got new energy and the rest of the match turned into an unstoppable storm.\n\nThe goal gave the team wings. The game changed, the crowd joined in, and before you knew it, it was 3-1 for Indonesia. A victory you want to relive.\n\n![Isa Warps with the ball](/images/gallery/Isa-warps-aan-de-bal-Sea-games.jpg)\n\n## The impactful goal and the coach's quote\n\nWhat did head coach Akira Higashiyama say afterwards? With pride and ambition:\n\n*\"This is Indonesia. I am proud of my players and we did well. But the 3-1 victory is not enough yet. We need to improve a lot. If we survive the group stage, we fully focus on the next match and the ultimate goal is to win the SEA Games.\"*\n\nHe didn't give in to complacency, looked ahead and made it clear that the team is not satisfied with one good match.\n\n![Isa Warps' goal](/images/gallery/Isa-Warps-Sea-Games-Goal.jpg)\n\n## The impact on the team\n\nThat victory brought Indonesia closer to the next round. It was a turning point: the team grew, team spirit became stronger and the will to continue greater. This was no coincidence, this was character.\n\n## What does this mean for the future?\n\nThe feeling of pride flowing through the stadium shows how women's football in Indonesia is growing. Young girls are already dreaming of moments like these, moments where you give everything and write history.\n\nFor Isa Warps, this is just the beginning. One night in Thailand, but the road to even greater moments lies straight ahead.\n\n![Isa with her father](/images/gallery/Isa-Warps-en-haar-vader.jpg)\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe cheering rolling through the stands, the tension that keeps a crowd silent, and then that one strike from Isa Warps that turns the match upside down. What a moment.\n\nThis is not just sport. It's passion, emotion and the soul of the game. This is what makes the SEA Games so special, what makes football unforgettable. And that's why we keep watching, cheering and dreaming.",
